     <div type="to_God">
   <pb facs="8"/>
   <head>To GOD.</head>
   <l>GLorious and Great; whose power did divide</l>
   <l>The <hi>Waves,</hi> and made them <hi>Walls</hi> on either side;</l>
   <l>That didst appeare in <hi>Cloven-tongues</hi> of <hi>Fyre;</hi>
   </l>
   <l>Divide my thoughts: and with thy selfe, inspire</l>
   <l>My soule; O cleave my <hi>Tongue,</hi> and make it scatter</l>
   <l>Various <hi>Expressions</hi> in a various <hi>Matter;</hi>
   </l>
   <l>That like the painefull <hi>Bee,</hi> I may derive</l>
   <l>From sundry <hi>Flow'rs,</hi> to store my slender <hi>Hive:</hi>
   </l>
   <l>Yet, may my Thoughts <hi>not so divided be,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>But they may mixe againe, and fixe in <hi>Thee.</hi>
   </l>
</div>
